        hindi_translation: 'मैं आपके मुख को कामदेव का चार पहियों वाला रथ मानता हूँ, जिसके दो पहिये आपके चमकते गालों पर प्रतिबिंबित होते दो कुण्डल हैं। इसी पर चढ़कर महावीर कामदेव, शिवजी के विरुद्ध युद्ध के लिए तैयार होता है।',
        english_translation: 'I consider this face of yours to be the four-wheeled chariot of Manmatha (Kamadeva), with the pair of your ear-ornaments reflected on your glittering cheeks as its two wheels. Mounting this, the great hero Mara (Kama) prepares to fight against the lord of the Pramathas (Shiva).',
        commentary: 'The Goddess\'s beautiful face itself is described as the chariot of the god of love, from which he wages his war even against the great Lord Shiva, highlighting her supreme power of enchantment.'
