        english_translation: 'O Sharvani! Seated on the crest of a great jeweled throne, constantly watching the earth which is made resonant with praises by thousands of gods bowing with their heads—Salutations to you! You protect even the Guru of the three worlds (Shiva).',
        commentary: 'The Goddess is depicted as the supreme sovereign, worshipped by all gods, who is so powerful that she is the protector of even her own consort, Lord Shiva.'
